SORTSMILL-CHANGELOGGER(1)        User Commands       SORTSMILL-CHANGELOGGER(1)



NAME
       sortsmill-changelogger - Sorts Mill Changelogger

SYNOPSIS
       sortsmill-changelogger [OPTION]...

DESCRIPTION
       Creates a GNU-style ChangeLog file from a version control log.

       -C DIR change to repository base directory DIR

       -h     display this help and exit

       -V     output version information and exit

       Unless you use the '-C' flag, sortsmill-changelogger expects to be run
       in a repository's base directory.

AUTHOR
       Written by Barry Schwartz.

REPORTING BUGS
       Report sortsmill-changelogger bugs at
       http://bitbucket.org/sortsmill/sortsmill-changelogger/issues
       Sorts Mill Changelogger home page:
       http://bitbucket.org/sortsmill/sortsmill-changelogger

